Patient: What exercises can I do to help with my heart failure?

Healthcare Educator: Great question! Low-impact activities like swimming, walking, or yoga are good for your heart.

Patient: I'm not really a swimmer. What other options do I have?

Healthcare Educator: That's okay! Walking daily or doing gentle yoga at home can be very beneficial.

Patient: I'm worried about starting. What if I can't keep up?

Healthcare Educator: Start slow. Even a 10-minute walk daily can make a difference. You can gradually increase your time.

Patient: I'm not sure I can motivate myself.

Healthcare Educator: Consider hiring a trainer or joining a seniors' exercise group. It can be fun and motivating!

Patient: How does exercise help my heart exactly?

Healthcare Educator: Exercise improves your heart's health, reduces symptoms, and boosts your overall quality of life.